 Requirements:
 -------------
 The install requires WHDLoad and RAWDIC to be in the path. Both can be found
 in the WHDLoad package.
 To install from a different drive than DF0: select installation mode Expert.
 
 The installed program requires 0.5 MB ChipMem (+.8Mb other memory for preload 
 option).
 
 It can be quit by pressing HELP (key can be changed with Tooltype "QuitKey=").
 
 The installed program requires WHDLoad 10+


 Thanks to Chris Vella for sending the original.


 Features:
 ---------
 - System friendly imager
 - Press 'F10' to quit.
 - Fixed 3 access faults
 - Saves scores to HD
 - Icons by Irek´72
 - Custom1 bits (high scores not saved)
 	Infinite lives: bit 0 (+1)
 	Infinite gernades: bit 1 (+2)
 	Near invincibility: bit 2 (+4)
    Press Help or forward+yellow to skip level: bit 3 (+8)
    (set to 255 to enable all features)
 - Custom3=1 Disable blitter patches
 - Custom2=1 Enable blue/second button to launch grenades
   (long press on fire button is then disabled)
 - CD32 joypad support:
	Red 			- Fire
	Play 			- Pause (press fire to unpause) 
	Play+Forward+Reverse 	- Quit
	Forward+Reverse+Green 	- Abort Game
	Forward+Yellow	- Skip level (Custom1=8)
 
    On Title screen
    	Forward			- Maps to F2
    	Reverse			- Maps ro F1


 History:
 --------
 version 1.3 (12.04.2020) done by JOTD:
 - custom2=1 allows that blue/second button launches grenades
 - proper joypad/joystick detection (issue #0004225)
 - grouped all trainer options to custom1 bits
 - changed skip level joypad control
 - save hiscore disabled if cheats are on
 
 version 1.2 (10.01.2012) done by Keith Krellwitz (Abaddon):
 - Complete re-write (removed jst macros and implemented PATCHLIST)
 - 4 more blitter waits added
 - Custom4=1 Enable 2nd trainer - invincibility and level skip
   press 'Help'
 - Fixed another access fault
 - Fixed 14x snoop bugs (long read from dff000)
 - Icons by Irek´72
 - Custom2=1 Disable blitter patches
 - Custom3=1 Enable CD32 support
	Red 			- Fire
	Play 			- Pause (press fire to unpause) 
	Yellow			- Skip levels when cheat active 
	Play+Forward+Reverse 	- Quit
	Forward+Reverse+Green 	- Abort Game
	Reverse+Green+Yellow	- Skip level (Custom4=1)
 
    On Title screen
    	Forward			- Maps to F2
    	Reverse			- Maps ro F1
    	
 version 1.1 (03.01.2002) done by Keith Krellwitz (Abaddon):
 - initial WHDLoad version
 - Press 'F10' to quit.
 - System friendly disk imager.
 - Trainer - Custom1=1 infinite lives and gernades - no highscores saved
 - Load/Save scores to hard drive
 - 8x blitter waits added
 - Fixed 2 access faults

 Contact:
 --------
 If you have problems with this installation please try and get a newer
 version of this package from the WHDLoad WWW-Page. If that doesn't help try
 some Tooltypes like NOCACHE, NOAUTOVEC, EXPCHIP, NOMMU, PAL or NTSC. If
 that also fails, please inform the author via the Bug-Report-Form which
 can be accessed on the WHDLoad WWW-Page or create a mantis issue directly
 at http://mantis.whdload.de

 For the full WHDLoad package, other installs and updates refer to:
	http://www.whdload.de/
 or	aminet:dev/misc/whdload#?
 and	aminet:game/patch/

